---
description: Backend conventions for Spring Boot + Spring Modulith
globs: ["backend/src/**/*.java"]
alwaysApply: false
---
- Flyway migrations are append-only — NEVER modify an existing migration file.
- Entities live in module sub-packages (internal). DTOs and controllers live in module root package (public).
- Use UUID primary keys with gen_random_uuid().
- Effective-dated records (rate_card, fx_rate) need overlap exclusion constraints via btree_gist.
- Partial unique index required for nullable unique columns (e.g. rate_card_line flat uniqueness).
- One aggregate root per repository. No cross-module repository injection.
- Validation annotations on all request DTOs.